<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="404" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,2013,2038]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,431]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="404" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">
The round and soft bodies have a thick tunic often covered with epibionts. The dorsal side and the siphons are often red in life. The siphons are distant of 1/3 of the body length and their aperture shows blue and red iridescent colours and white spots (
<figureCitation box="[341,457,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,822,844]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,193,801]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[150,1436,193,801]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herdmania pallida. A, dissection, scale bar = 1cm; B, anus and gonoducts (stained)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458742/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 4A,B</figureCitation>
). The dorsal tubercle is large with inrolled horns. The dorsal lamina has sharp languets. The branchial sac has an average of 9 high folds on the right side and sometimes there is a 10th incomplete fold, and a fold less on the left side. The hepatic gland is divided into 3 parts: 2 lobes on each side of the cardia and a larger lobe covering the pyloric side of the stomach (
<figureCitation box="[669,759,298,323]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,822,844]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,193,801]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[150,1436,193,801]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herdmania pallida. A, dissection, scale bar = 1cm; B, anus and gonoducts (stained)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458742/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). The gut loop is high and widely opened (
<figureCitation box="[1236,1326,298,323]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,822,844]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,193,801]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[150,1436,193,801]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herdmania pallida. A, dissection, scale bar = 1cm; B, anus and gonoducts (stained)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458742/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). There is one tubular and straight gonad on each body side (
<figureCitation box="[732,824,334,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,822,844]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,193,801]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[150,1436,193,801]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herdmania pallida. A, dissection, scale bar = 1cm; B, anus and gonoducts (stained)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458742/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Oviduct and sperm duct open close to each other in simple holes. The anus has a smooth edge (
<figureCitation box="[634,722,370,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,822,844]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,193,801]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[150,1436,193,801]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Herdmania pallida. A, dissection, scale bar = 1cm; B, anus and gonoducts (stained)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458742/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). There is a large velum at both siphon apertures. All tissues are filled with acicular spicules.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
